  "A company's profit is P(x) = x * (500 - 2x) dollars, where x is units sold. Using the product rule, find the marginal profit at x = 100 units.": "",
  "$50 per unit": "",
  "$100 per unit": "",
  "$200 per unit": "",
  "$300 per unit": "",
  "P'(x) = (1)(500 - 2x) + x(-2) = 500 - 2x - 2x = 500 - 4x. At x = 100: P'(100) = 500 - 400 = $100 per unit.": "",
  "A pharmacist models a drug's effectiveness as E(t) = 100t/(t^2 + 25) percent, where t is hours after taking the drug. Using the quotient rule, at what time is the effectiveness maximized (E'(t) = 0)?": "",
  "t = 5 hours": "",
  "t = 7 hours": "",
  "t = 3 hours": "",
  "t = 10 hours": "",
  "E'(t) = [100(t^2+25) - 100t(2t)]/(t^2+25)^2 = 100(25 - t^2)/(t^2+25)^2. Setting E'(t) = 0: 25 - t^2 = 0, so t = 5 hours.": "",
  "A balloon's volume and radius are changing. If V = (4/3)pi*r^3 and r(t) = 2t + 1 cm, find dV/dt at t = 1 second using the product/chain rule approach.": "",
