  "A marketing firm models ad revenue as R(x) = x * sqrt(100 - x) thousand dollars, where x is thousands spent on advertising. What is the marginal revenue at x = 36?": "",
  "$3.50 thousand per thousand spent": "",
  "$8.00 thousand per thousand spent": "",
  "$5.75 thousand per thousand spent": "",
  "$6.25 thousand per thousand spent": "",
  "R'(x) = sqrt(100-x) + x * (-1)/(2*sqrt(100-x)) = sqrt(100-x) - x/(2*sqrt(100-x)). At x = 36: sqrt(64) = 8, so R'(36) = 8 - 36/16 = 8 - 2.25 = 5.75 thousand dollars per thousand spent.": ""
